  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN175.2-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">piriviṉkaṇ vaṟpuṟuttiya <gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="6"/>rac colliyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">What ____ said to _________ who consoled [her] during the separation.</p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN175.2">
      <lg type="edition">
        <l>vīṅkuviḷim puṟīiya vicaippamai <supplied>nōṉcilai</supplied></l>
        <l><supplied>vāṅkuto</supplied>ṭai piḻaiyā <supplied>va</supplied>ṉka ṇāṭavar</l>
        <l>viṭutoṟum viḷikkum vevvāy vāḷi</l>
        <l>yāṟucel vampala ruyircelvap peyarppiṟ</l>
        <l>pāṟukiḷai payirntu paṭumuṭai <supplied>kavarum</supplied></l>
        <l><supplied>veñcura miṟanta</supplied> kātalar neñcuṇa</l>
        <l>variya vañciṉañ colliyum paṉmāṇ</l>
        <l>ṭērvaḷai muṉkai paṟṟiyum viṉaimuṭittu</l>
        <l>varutu meṉṟaṉa raṉṟō tōḻi</l>
        <l>kāliya ṉe<supplied>ṭuntērk kaivaṇ ceḻi</supplied>ya</l>
        <l>ṉālaṅ kāṉat tamarkaṭan tuyartta</l>
        <l>vēliṉum pallūḻ miṉṉi muraceṉa</l>
        <l>māyiru vicumpiṟ kaṭiyiṭi payiṟṟi</l>
        <l>nērkatir niraitta nēmiyañ celvaṉ</l>
        <l><supplied>pōraṭaṅ kakalam poruntiya tār</supplied>pōṟ</l>
        <l>ṟiruvi ṟē<supplied>e</supplied>ttuk kulaii yurukeḻu</l>
        <l>maṇpayam pūppap pāya</l>
        <l>taṇpeya leḻili tāḻnta poḻutē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
        <l>[Our] lover who has gone to cross the hot desert, (6a-c)</l>
        <l>where, when the strong men who do not fail in shooting when bending (2)</l>
        <l>[their] sturdy bows speedy so as to graze the swelling border(?), (1)</l>
        <l>remove the lives [and] wealth of strangers going [that] way (4)</l>
        <l>with cruel-mouthed arrows that whistle whenever sent off, (3)</l>
        <l>kites call [their] relatives [and] seize the fallen flesh, (5)</l>
        <l>he spoke difficult oaths while [my] heart absorbed [them], (6d-7c)</l>
        <l>fully gripped [my] forearms with beautiful bangles (7d-8c)</l>
        <l>and said “we will come [back] after finishing the work” – isn’t it, friend? – (8d-9c)</l>
        <l>– at the time when the clouds hover with cool rains (18)</l>
        <l>in order to spread so that the yield of the earth blooms, (17)</l>
        <l>fearfully shaking the land of the brilliant bow, (16)</l>
        <l>that resembles the garland to be joined to the chest to which they yield in fight (15)</l>
        <l>of the lord with the discus(?) that lines up straight rays, (14)</l>
        <l>repeating speedy thunder in the vast dark sky (13)</l>
        <l>like a drum, flashing many more times than [there were] spears (12)</l>
        <l>that were raised when being victorious in the battle at Ālaṅkāṉam (11)</l>
        <l>by Ceḻiyaṉ generous of hand, with a large chariot moving [like] the wind. (10)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
